<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
    <title>Suspicious Login Activity</title>
</head>
<body style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #f1f5f9; padding: 40px;">
<table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"
       style="max-width: 600px; margin: auto; background: #ffffff; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); overflow: hidden;">
    <tr>
        <td style="padding: 32px;">
            <h2 style="margin-top: 0; color: #18181b; font-size: 20px; text-align: center">
                We noticed a suspicious login attempt
            </h2>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; color: #3f3f46; line-height: 1.5; text-align: center">
                Someone tried to refresh your session from a device or location we didn’t recognize.
            </p>

            <table style="margin: 24px auto; font-size: 14px; color: #3f3f46;">
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>IP Address:</strong></td>
                    <td>{{ip}}</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Device:</strong></td>
                    <td>{{userAgent}}</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Time:</strong></td>
                    <td>{{timestamp}}</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <p style="font-size: 15px; color: #3f3f46; text-align: center;">
                If this was you, you can safely ignore this message.
                <br/><br/>
                If this wasn’t you, we recommend logging in again and checking your devices.
            </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

<p style="font-size: 12px; text-align: center; color: #a1a1aa; margin-top: 30px;">
    You’re receiving this email because your account activity triggered a security alert.
</p>
</body>
</html>
